      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a fifth-year PhD student in Psychology at Brandeis University. I work with Dr. Jennifer Gutsell in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.brandeis.edu/psychology/gutsell/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Social Interaction and Motivation lab&lt;/a&gt;, where I use a variety of methods including electroencephalography (EEG), traditional psychological questionnaires, implicit measures, and structural and hierarchical modeling to study group biases and dehumanzation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I previously worked at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facinghistory.org&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Facing History and Ourselves&lt;/a&gt;, and am still dedicated to teaching about and trying to prevent humanity&amp;rsquo;s worst behaviors. When not researching or teaching, I do other things, like &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/user/HarvardVoiceLab&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;singing&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
